Company Profile:ASM Assembly SystemsThe SIPLACE team is a unit of ASM Pacific Technology operating under the ASM Assembly Systems name. With its SIPLACE machines and innovative manufacturing concepts, ASM Assembly Systems GmbH & Co. KG is the world’s leading manufacturer of surface mount technology (SMT) placement machines and solutions. Since its beginnings in 1985, the company has installed almost 35,000 SIPLACE placement machines at more than 3,500 customers worldwide. Electronics manufacturers in all industries such as telecommunications, automotive, IT, consumer electronics and automation use and depend on SIPLACE’s broad portfolio of solutions and services.For more information about ASM Assembly Systems (SIPLACE), visit www.siplace.com.
Job Description:Objective:To learn and acquire a better understanding of Marketing Communications in the context of surface mount technology (SMT) industry and its impact on business.To develop analytical, organizational skills and interpersonal skills through product marketing activities.Tasks and Responsibilities:To provide support for trade shows – preparation, execution and follow up actionsSupport on Korean customer magazine Support on branding itemsShort news – create short news for website and eNewsletterSupport on several internal marketing plans Requirements:Good interpersonal and communication skillsAble to multitask with several projectsAble to work both independently and as a teamAble to adapt and work actively in new environmentFluent in both English and KoreanProficient in MS Office ApplicationsAdditional Benefits/Information:Opportunity to meet people and work in a multicultural environmentChance to utilize both Korean and English in a working environment
